def detect_lang_safe(text):
    try:
        return detect(str(text))
    except:
        return "unknown"

data["lang"] = data["Statement"].apply(detect_lang_safe)

# Keep only English & Dutch
data = data[data["lang"].isin(["en","nl"])]
print(data["lang"].value_counts())

In[10]:
stop_words = set(stopwords.words("english")) | set(stopwords.words("dutch"))

def clean_text(text):
    text = str(text).lower()
    text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z]+', ' ', text)
    tokens = [w for w in text.split() if w not in stop_words and len(w) > 2]
    return tokens

data["tokens"] = data["Statement"].apply(clean_text)

In[13]:
def plot_word_freq(data_subset, title):
    all_tokens = [t for tokens in data_subset["tokens"] for t in tokens]
    if not all_tokens:
        print(f"No tokens to plot for {title}")
        return
    freq = Counter(all_tokens).most_common(15)
    words, counts = zip(*freq)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    plt.bar(words, counts, color="skyblue", edgecolor="black")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

data_en = data[data["lang"]=="en"]
data_nl = data[data["lang"]=="nl"]

plot_word_freq(data_en, "Top Words in English Statements")
plot_word_freq(data_nl, "Top Words in Dutch Statements")
In[14]:
def make_wordcloud(data_subset, title):
    all_tokens = [t for tokens in data_subset["tokens"] for t in tokens]
    if not all_tokens:
        print(f"No tokens to make word cloud for {title}")
        return
    text = " ".join(all_tokens)
    wc = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color="white").generate(text)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation="bilinear")
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()


make_wordcloud(data_en, "Word Cloud - English")
make_wordcloud(data_nl, "Word Cloud - Dutch")
In[15]:
def lexical_diversity(tokens):
    if len(tokens) == 0:
        return 0
    return len(set(tokens)) / len(tokens)

for lang in ["en", "nl"]:
    subset = data[data["lang"] == lang]
    lex_div_by_type = subset.groupby("Type")["tokens"].apply(
        lambda x: lexical_diversity([w for tokens in x for w in tokens])
    )
    print(f"\nLexical diversity in {lang.upper()} by type:\n", lex_div_by_type)

    lex_div_by_type.plot(kind="bar", figsize=(8,5), color="orange", edgecolor="black")
    plt.title(f"Lexical Diversity by Type - {lang.upper()}")
    plt.ylabel("Unique / Total Word Ratio")
    plt.show()

Clustering & Similarity (TF-IDF)

In[27]:
# Convert text to TF-IDF english words
tfidf_en = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words="english", ngram_range=(1,2), min_df=2)
X_en = tfidf_en.fit_transform(statements_en)
In[38]:
# Cluster into groups (choose e.g. 5 clusters)
k_en = min(5, X_en.shape[0])  # keep k valid if EN set is small
kmeans_en = KMeans(n_clusters=k_en, random_state=42, n_init=10)
data_en = data_en.copy()        
data_en["Cluster"] = kmeans_en.fit_predict(X_en)
